! JSON Convert

</div>

A TiddlyWiki plugin that turns arbitrary JSON into tiddlers, with
reusable profiles, a preview-and-commit staging area, and
tolerant input handling.

This is the demo wiki.  The plugin is loaded, six sample profiles
and their matching data are pre-installed, and the Console is one
click away.

! Try it

Click here — 
<$button class="tc-btn-invisible" tooltip="Open the Console">
  <$action-navigate $to="$:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/Console"/>{{$:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/icon}}
</$button> 
— or use the matching icon in the page-controls toolbar (top-right of the page), or 
open [[JSON Convert Console]] directly.

Workflow: paste matching JSON into the source area, pick a profile,
click ''Convert'', review the staged tiddlers, click ''Apply''.

! Installing the plugin in your own wiki

Drag the tiddler [[$:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert]] onto your own
wiki and save.  A {{$:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/icon}} icon
appears in the page-controls toolbar.  When you've finished doing
your import, you can keep JSON_Convert around for next time or
remove it, as you prefer. 

! Documentation

For a full walkthrough — Console workflow, profile schema,
path expressions, transforms, the profile editor, recipes, and a
reference — see the [[Usage guide|$:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/usage]].

