! How a profile works

A profile is a small JSON document:

```
{
  "records": "{{books[*]}}",
  "tw-fields": {
    "title": "{{author}}: {{title}}",
    "tags":  "Book {{genre|split-commas}}"
  },
  "custom-fields": {
    "year": "{{year}}"
  }
}
```

* ''records'' points at the array of source records — one tiddler
  per element.
* ''tw-fields'' / ''custom-fields'' describe what each tiddler's
  fields look like.  `{{path}}` tokens resolve against the current
  record; `{{path|transform}}` pipes through a named transform.
* When ''records'' crosses multiple `[*]`s, bindings can use
  `{{../field}}` to reach the enclosing scope (see the Trip
  Itinerary and Music Library samples).

For wide source schemas, the editor's Custom Fields header has a ''Pick fields…'' button that opens a checkbox tree of every leaf in the source — tick to add as pass-through bindings, untick the cruft.  Try it on the Moodle Gradebook sample.

Open any sample profile via the Console's ''Edit'' button to see
the form-based editor.

! Transforms

Tokens can pipe their value through a named transform —
`{{name|slugify}}`, chained left-to-right as `{{x|to-string|slugify}}`.
The plugin ships with:

* ''html-to-wikitext'', ''split-commas'', ''split-to-titles'',
  ''timestamp-to-date'' — JS built-ins compiled into the engine.
* ''to-upper-case'', ''to-lower-case'', ''to-title-case'',
  ''slugify'' — short wikitext transforms in the plugin's
  `transforms/` folder.

To add your own, drop a tiddler tagged
`$:/tags/json-convert/transform`.  Two body languages are supported:
JavaScript (`type: application/javascript`) for arbitrary logic, and
wikitext (`type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki`) for filter / template
expressions.  The Browse modal's transform picker shows everything
available.  See the [[usage guide|$:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/usage]]
for details.


